<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="67" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1277,2022]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,446,1278,1302]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">
Male 
<typeStatus box="[266,371,1278,1302]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">holotype</typeStatus>
. Head
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[461,543,1277,1301]" captionStart="FIGURE 2 a – e" captionStartId="2.[151,249,1837,1860]" captionTargetBox="[155,1421,245,1779]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[152,1434,193,1816]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2 a – e. Heteropodagrion croizati (a) male holotype, head in dorsal view; (b) male holotype prothorax in dorsal view; (c) male holotype, pterothorax in lateral view; (d) male holotype, fore wing; (e) hind wing, male holotype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/277130/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">
Fig. 
<number box="[513,529,1277,1301]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" value="2.0">2</number>
a
</figureCitation>
): labrum white with distal margin black, anteclypeus white, postclypeus shining black, genae brown, mandibles caramel, frons shining black with two prominent lobes separated by a dark midline. Vertex black, postocular spots absent, occiput brown, shallow. Occipital margin with a sparse row of long hairs.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1277,2022]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,319,1386,1410]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">Prothorax</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[334,417,1385,1409]" captionStart="FIGURE 2 a – e" captionStartId="2.[151,249,1837,1860]" captionTargetBox="[155,1421,245,1779]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[152,1434,193,1816]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2 a – e. Heteropodagrion croizati (a) male holotype, head in dorsal view; (b) male holotype prothorax in dorsal view; (c) male holotype, pterothorax in lateral view; (d) male holotype, fore wing; (e) hind wing, male holotype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/277130/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">
Fig. 
<number box="[386,402,1385,1409]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" value="2.0">2</number>
b
</figureCitation>
): in dorsal view brown with pale sides, anterior lobe with anterior margin smooth. In lateral view propleuron dark with prominent lobes. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[691,845,1422,1446]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">Pterothorax:</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[867,954,1421,1445]" captionStart="FIGURE 2 a – e" captionStartId="2.[151,249,1837,1860]" captionTargetBox="[155,1421,245,1779]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[152,1434,193,1816]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2 a – e. Heteropodagrion croizati (a) male holotype, head in dorsal view; (b) male holotype prothorax in dorsal view; (c) male holotype, pterothorax in lateral view; (d) male holotype, fore wing; (e) hind wing, male holotype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/277130/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">
Fig. 
<number box="[926,941,1421,1445]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" value="2.0">2</number>
c
</figureCitation>
) largely brown with metepisternum and metepimeron pale. Mesostigmal plate without hairs. Middorsal carina brown. Mesepisternum with a complete narrow yellow antehumeral stripe. Mesinfraepisternum brown, becoming darker next to mesothoracic suture and reddish towards mesocoxa. Mesepimeron entirely brown. Metinfraepisternum pale. Metepisternum pale with a wide dark brown stripe on metapleural suture. Metepimeron largely pale, in ventral view venter of thorax completely yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1277,2022]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,262,1638,1662]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">Legs:</emphasis>
pro-, meso- and metacoxa reddish, metafemur (
<quantity box="[801,883,1637,1661]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.2" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" unit="mm" value="4.2">4.2mm</quantity>
) with inner row of 
<number box="[1101,1129,1637,1661]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" value="10.0">10</number>
setiform spines, increasing in length toward tibia. Tibiae reddish externally, armed with 
<number box="[862,876,1673,1697]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" value="9.0">9</number>
long setiform spurs. Tarsal claw with subapical tooth, inner tooth approximately half length of outer tooth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1277,2022]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,282,1745,1770]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">Wings:</emphasis>
hyaline, venation black, Pt magenta, slightly larger in Hw, covering more than two cells, proximal side oblique, petiolation reaching level of arculus. Two supplementary sectors between IR 
<number box="[1136,1150,1781,1805]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" value="2.0">2</number>
- 
<collectingCountry box="[1167,1203,1781,1805]" name="Poland" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">RP</collectingCountry>
<number box="[1204,1216,1781,1805]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" value="3.0">3</number>
and between 
<collectingCountry box="[1378,1415,1781,1805]" name="Poland" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">RP</collectingCountry>
<number box="[1415,1429,1781,1805]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" value="2.0">2</number>
- IR 
<number box="[182,196,1817,1841]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" value="2.0">2</number>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1277,2022]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,234,1854,1878]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">Fw</emphasis>
(
<quantity box="[250,349,1853,1877]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7199999999999998" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" unit="mm" value="27.2">27.2mm</quantity>
): (
<figureCitation box="[377,462,1853,1877]" captionStart="FIGURE 2 a – e" captionStartId="2.[151,249,1837,1860]" captionTargetBox="[155,1421,245,1779]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[152,1434,193,1816]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2 a – e. Heteropodagrion croizati (a) male holotype, head in dorsal view; (b) male holotype prothorax in dorsal view; (c) male holotype, pterothorax in lateral view; (d) male holotype, fore wing; (e) hind wing, male holotype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/277130/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">
Fig. 
<number box="[430,446,1853,1877]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" value="2.0">2</number>
d
</figureCitation>
): two complete Ax, 
<number box="[693,721,1853,1877]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" value="21.0">21</number>
Px, IR 
<number box="[803,816,1853,1877]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" value="2.0">2</number>
arising little after subnodus, 
<collectingCountry box="[1147,1182,1853,1877]" name="Poland" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">RP</collectingCountry>
<number box="[1183,1196,1853,1877]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" value="2.0">2</number>
arising between seventh and eighth Px, 
<collectingCountry box="[382,418,1889,1913]" name="Poland" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">RP</collectingCountry>
<number box="[418,459,1889,1913]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3–4</number>
arising little before subnodus; 
<collectionCode box="[817,871,1889,1913]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/rgag-nxxe" name="Catholic University of Peking" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">CUP</collectionCode>
close to first complete Ax. CUA arising close to second Ax; MA arising little after second Ax; IR 
<number box="[703,713,1925,1949]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" value="1.0">1</number>
arising close to ninth or tenth Px.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1277,2022]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,239,1962,1986]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">Hw</emphasis>
(
<quantity box="[254,329,1961,1985]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" unit="mm" value="27.0">27mm</quantity>
) (
<figureCitation box="[353,434,1961,1985]" captionStart="FIGURE 2 a – e" captionStartId="2.[151,249,1837,1860]" captionTargetBox="[155,1421,245,1779]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[152,1434,193,1816]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2 a – e. Heteropodagrion croizati (a) male holotype, head in dorsal view; (b) male holotype prothorax in dorsal view; (c) male holotype, pterothorax in lateral view; (d) male holotype, fore wing; (e) hind wing, male holotype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/277130/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">
Fig. 
<number box="[407,421,1961,1985]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" value="2.0">2</number>
e
</figureCitation>
) two complete Ax, 
<number box="[661,689,1961,1985]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" value="19.0">19</number>
Px, 
<collectingCountry box="[741,776,1961,1985]" name="Poland" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">RP</collectingCountry>
<number box="[776,789,1961,1985]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" value="2.0">2</number>
arising between fifth and sixth Px, 
<collectingCountry box="[1195,1231,1961,1985]" name="Poland" pageId="1" pageNumber="64">RP</collectingCountry>
<number box="[1231,1272,1961,1985]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3–4</number>
arising before subnodus, IR 
<number box="[299,312,1998,2022]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" value="2.0">2</number>
arising a little after subnodus; IR 
<number box="[692,701,1998,2022]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" value="1.0">1</number>
arising at eighth Px.
</paragraph>
