, including appendages): abdominal segments largely brown, with basal pale ring in all segments. Dorsally, posterior margin of S 
<number box="[587,616,1961,1985]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="10.0">10</number>
medially recessed (
<figureCitation box="[843,924,1961,1985]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 2 a – e" captionStart-1="FIGURE 2 f – k" captionStartId-0="2.[151,249,1837,1860]" captionStartId-1="3.[151,250,1802,1825]" captionTargetBox-0="[155,1421,245,1779]" captionTargetBox-1="[159,1411,226,1761]" captionTargetId-0="figure@2.[152,1434,193,1816]" captionTargetId-1="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1781]" captionTargetPageId-0="2" captionTargetPageId-1="3" captionText-0="FIGURE 2 a – e. Heteropodagrion croizati (a) male holotype, head in dorsal view; (b) male holotype prothorax in dorsal view; (c) male holotype, pterothorax in lateral view; (d) male holotype, fore wing; (e) hind wing, male holotype." captionText-1="FIGURE 2 f – k. Heteropodagrion croizati (f) distal portion of abdomen, male holotype, dorsal view; (g) distal portion of abdomen, holotype; lateral view; (h) genital ligula, holotype, frontal view; (i) genital ligula, holotype, lateral view; (j) distal portion of abdomen, female allotype, lateral view; (k) distal portion of abdomen, female allotype, ventral view." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/277130/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/277131/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">
Fig. 
<number box="[897,912,1961,1985]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="2.0">2</number>
f
</figureCitation>
), cerci brown, in dorsal view slightly curved inwards, with rounded and slightly flattened tips, external margin armed with small spines, distal region with an excavation, in lateral view directed medio-ventrally and wide at base (
<figureCitation box="[972,1054,151,175]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 2 a – e" captionStart-1="FIGURE 2 f – k" captionStartId-0="2.[151,249,1837,1860]" captionStartId-1="3.[151,250,1802,1825]" captionTargetBox-0="[155,1421,245,1779]" captionTargetBox-1="[159,1411,226,1761]" captionTargetId-0="figure@2.[152,1434,193,1816]" captionTargetId-1="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1781]" captionTargetPageId-0="2" captionTargetPageId-1="3" captionText-0="FIGURE 2 a – e. Heteropodagrion croizati (a) male holotype, head in dorsal view; (b) male holotype prothorax in dorsal view; (c) male holotype, pterothorax in lateral view; (d) male holotype, fore wing; (e) hind wing, male holotype." captionText-1="FIGURE 2 f – k. Heteropodagrion croizati (f) distal portion of abdomen, male holotype, dorsal view; (g) distal portion of abdomen, holotype; lateral view; (h) genital ligula, holotype, frontal view; (i) genital ligula, holotype, lateral view; (j) distal portion of abdomen, female allotype, lateral view; (k) distal portion of abdomen, female allotype, ventral view." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/277130/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/277131/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
Fig. 
<number box="[1028,1043,151,175]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="2.0">2</number>
f
</figureCitation>
); paraprocts elongate, surpassing length of cercus, wide at base, with dorsal margin sclerotized and prominent, and with slender and rounded tips. In lateral view directed upwards (
<figureCitation box="[497,581,223,247]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 2 a – e" captionStart-1="FIGURE 2 f – k" captionStartId-0="2.[151,249,1837,1860]" captionStartId-1="3.[151,250,1802,1825]" captionTargetBox-0="[155,1421,245,1779]" captionTargetBox-1="[159,1411,226,1761]" captionTargetId-0="figure@2.[152,1434,193,1816]" captionTargetId-1="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1781]" captionTargetPageId-0="2" captionTargetPageId-1="3" captionText-0="FIGURE 2 a – e. Heteropodagrion croizati (a) male holotype, head in dorsal view; (b) male holotype prothorax in dorsal view; (c) male holotype, pterothorax in lateral view; (d) male holotype, fore wing; (e) hind wing, male holotype." captionText-1="FIGURE 2 f – k. Heteropodagrion croizati (f) distal portion of abdomen, male holotype, dorsal view; (g) distal portion of abdomen, holotype; lateral view; (h) genital ligula, holotype, frontal view; (i) genital ligula, holotype, lateral view; (j) distal portion of abdomen, female allotype, lateral view; (k) distal portion of abdomen, female allotype, ventral view." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/277130/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/277131/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[549,581,223,247]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="2.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" unit="g" value="2.0">2g</quantity>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,752]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,360,259,284]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">Genital ligula</emphasis>
: inner fold well developed; shaft sclerotized along middle region, armed with 
<number box="[1253,1323,260,284]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="12.5" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="10.0">10–15</number>
short and thin spurs; apical segment membranous, tip slightly concave with bilobulate long trumpet-shaped extensions, surpassing middle region of ligula in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[682,785,332,356]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 2 a – e" captionStart-1="FIGURE 2 f – k" captionStartId-0="2.[151,249,1837,1860]" captionStartId-1="3.[151,250,1802,1825]" captionTargetBox-0="[155,1421,245,1779]" captionTargetBox-1="[159,1411,226,1761]" captionTargetId-0="figure@2.[152,1434,193,1816]" captionTargetId-1="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1781]" captionTargetPageId-0="2" captionTargetPageId-1="3" captionText-0="FIGURE 2 a – e. Heteropodagrion croizati (a) male holotype, head in dorsal view; (b) male holotype prothorax in dorsal view; (c) male holotype, pterothorax in lateral view; (d) male holotype, fore wing; (e) hind wing, male holotype." captionText-1="FIGURE 2 f – k. Heteropodagrion croizati (f) distal portion of abdomen, male holotype, dorsal view; (g) distal portion of abdomen, holotype; lateral view; (h) genital ligula, holotype, frontal view; (i) genital ligula, holotype, lateral view; (j) distal portion of abdomen, female allotype, lateral view; (k) distal portion of abdomen, female allotype, ventral view." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/277130/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/277131/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
Fig. 
<number box="[734,749,332,356]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="2.0">2</number>
h, i
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,752]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,397,368,392]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">Female allotype.</emphasis>
Coloration and wing venation as in male. IR 
<number box="[918,927,367,391]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="1.0">1</number>
arising at eighth Px in FW, at seventh Px in HW. Gonapophyses in dorsal view with distinctive, pale, scarcely sclerotized region between end of S 
<number box="[1309,1323,404,428]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="7.0">7</number>
and anterior margin of S 
<number box="[334,349,439,463]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="8.0">8</number>
; in lateral view tip of ovipositor not surpassing cercus, armed with minute spines ventrally (
<figureCitation captionStart-0="FIGURE 2 a – e" captionStart-1="FIGURE 2 f – k" captionStartId-0="2.[151,249,1837,1860]" captionStartId-1="3.[151,250,1802,1825]" captionTargetBox-0="[155,1421,245,1779]" captionTargetBox-1="[159,1411,226,1761]" captionTargetId-0="figure@2.[152,1434,193,1816]" captionTargetId-1="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1781]" captionTargetPageId-0="2" captionTargetPageId-1="3" captionText-0="FIGURE 2 a – e. Heteropodagrion croizati (a) male holotype, head in dorsal view; (b) male holotype prothorax in dorsal view; (c) male holotype, pterothorax in lateral view; (d) male holotype, fore wing; (e) hind wing, male holotype." captionText-1="FIGURE 2 f – k. Heteropodagrion croizati (f) distal portion of abdomen, male holotype, dorsal view; (g) distal portion of abdomen, holotype; lateral view; (h) genital ligula, holotype, frontal view; (i) genital ligula, holotype, lateral view; (j) distal portion of abdomen, female allotype, lateral view; (k) distal portion of abdomen, female allotype, ventral view." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/277130/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/277131/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,166,476,500]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="2.0">2</number>
j, k
</figureCitation>
); vulvar spine absent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,752]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,511,536]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">Variation.</emphasis>
Male 
<typeStatus box="[391,488,512,536]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">paratype</typeStatus>
as 
<typeStatus box="[526,624,511,535]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">holotype</typeStatus>
but metafemur (
<quantity box="[812,901,511,535]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.8" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" unit="mm" value="3.8">3.8 mm</quantity>
) with inner row of 
<number box="[1121,1149,511,535]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="12.0">12</number>
setiform spines, Fw with 
<number box="[151,179,548,572]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="23.0">23</number>
Px, Hw with 
<number box="[333,361,548,572]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="17.0">17</number>
Px.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="68" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,752]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,583,608]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[329,450,585,608]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteropodagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="croizati">
<emphasis box="[329,450,585,608]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">H. croizati</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from the other known species of the genus by the extremely long male paraprocts (
<figureCitation box="[346,452,620,644]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 2 a – e" captionStart-1="FIGURE 2 f – k" captionStartId-0="2.[151,249,1837,1860]" captionStartId-1="3.[151,250,1802,1825]" captionTargetBox-0="[155,1421,245,1779]" captionTargetBox-1="[159,1411,226,1761]" captionTargetId-0="figure@2.[152,1434,193,1816]" captionTargetId-1="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1781]" captionTargetPageId-0="2" captionTargetPageId-1="3" captionText-0="FIGURE 2 a – e. Heteropodagrion croizati (a) male holotype, head in dorsal view; (b) male holotype prothorax in dorsal view; (c) male holotype, pterothorax in lateral view; (d) male holotype, fore wing; (e) hind wing, male holotype." captionText-1="FIGURE 2 f – k. Heteropodagrion croizati (f) distal portion of abdomen, male holotype, dorsal view; (g) distal portion of abdomen, holotype; lateral view; (h) genital ligula, holotype, frontal view; (i) genital ligula, holotype, lateral view; (j) distal portion of abdomen, female allotype, lateral view; (k) distal portion of abdomen, female allotype, ventral view." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/277130/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/277131/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
Fig. 
<number box="[399,413,620,644]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="2.0">2</number>
f, g
</figureCitation>
) and male genital ligula distally bilobulate, trumpet-shaped, and with laterally expanding distal lobes (
<figureCitation box="[338,453,655,679]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 2 a – e" captionStart-1="FIGURE 2 f – k" captionStartId-0="2.[151,249,1837,1860]" captionStartId-1="3.[151,250,1802,1825]" captionTargetBox-0="[155,1421,245,1779]" captionTargetBox-1="[159,1411,226,1761]" captionTargetId-0="figure@2.[152,1434,193,1816]" captionTargetId-1="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1781]" captionTargetPageId-0="2" captionTargetPageId-1="3" captionText-0="FIGURE 2 a – e. Heteropodagrion croizati (a) male holotype, head in dorsal view; (b) male holotype prothorax in dorsal view; (c) male holotype, pterothorax in lateral view; (d) male holotype, fore wing; (e) hind wing, male holotype." captionText-1="FIGURE 2 f – k. Heteropodagrion croizati (f) distal portion of abdomen, male holotype, dorsal view; (g) distal portion of abdomen, holotype; lateral view; (h) genital ligula, holotype, frontal view; (i) genital ligula, holotype, lateral view; (j) distal portion of abdomen, female allotype, lateral view; (k) distal portion of abdomen, female allotype, ventral view." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/277130/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/277131/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
Fig. 
<date box="[391,429,655,679]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
<number box="[391,408,655,679]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="2.0">2</number>
. i
</date>
, j
</figureCitation>
). Other characters to diagnose this species are found in the wing venation; in Fw of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteropodagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sanquinipes">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">H. sanquinipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[343,489,692,716]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteropodagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="superbum">
<emphasis box="[343,489,692,716]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">H. superbum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
there are two long supplementary sectors between 
<collectingCountry box="[1079,1114,692,716]" name="Poland" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">RP</collectingCountry>
<number box="[1115,1128,692,716]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="2.0">2</number>
and IR 
<number box="[1217,1231,692,716]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="2.0">2</number>
, while 
<taxonomicName box="[1315,1436,693,716]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteropodagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="croizati">
<emphasis box="[1315,1436,693,716]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">H. croizati</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has just one very short sector there.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/277132/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" targetBox="[171,1404,812,1784]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1840,1986]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1840,1863]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">FIGURE 3.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[281,533,1841,1863]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Mesagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leucorrhinum">
<emphasis box="[281,533,1841,1863]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">Mesagrion leucorrhinum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(a) male forewing, COLOMBIA: Cundinamarca Dept, Guayabetal, alt. 1270 m, 1 Ƥ, 10- XII- 2007, L. A. Pérez, deposited at UARC, Barranquilla, Atlántico, Colombia (b) male hindwing same specimen (c) female prothorax, same data but 15- VI- 2010 (d) genital ligula in frontal view, same data but 15- VI- 2010; 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteropodagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="superbum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">Heteropodagrion superbum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(e) genital ligula in lateral view Risaralda Deparment. Tatamá, PNN [National Park] alt. 2000m, 15 vii 2010, deposited UARC, Barranquilla, Atlántico, Colombia (f) genital ligula, in frontal view same data.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,646]" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">
A large series of 
<taxonomicName box="[393,586,153,177]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteropodagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[393,586,153,177]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">Heteropodagrion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
identified as 
<taxonomicName box="[740,885,153,177]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteropodagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="superbum">
<emphasis box="[740,885,153,177]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">H. superbum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<number box="[902,931,152,176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" value="25.0">25</number>
ɗ, 
<number box="[973,987,152,176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" value="4.0">4</number>
Ψ) from Risaralda Deparment. Tatamá, PNN [National Park] alt. 
<quantity box="[448,529,189,213]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" unit="m" value="2000.0">2000m</quantity>
, 
<date box="[543,679,189,213]" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" value="2010-07-15">
<number box="[543,571,189,213]" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" value="15.0">15</number>
vii 
<number box="[620,679,189,213]" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" value="2010.0">2010</number>
</date>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[693,806,189,213]" name="Colombia" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, showed only a slight degree of curvature of the male cerci. However, 
<bibRefCitation box="[334,576,225,249]" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" refString="Garrison, R. W., von Ellenrieder, N. &amp; Louton, J. A. (2010) Damselfly Genera of the New World. An Illustrated and Annotated Key to the Zygoptera. The John Hopkins University Press. Baltimore. United States of America, xiv + 490 pp, + 24 pls" type="book">
Garrison 
<emphasis box="[439,494,225,249]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">et al.</emphasis>
(
<number box="[509,568,225,249]" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" value="2010.0">2010</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
indicated that species resolution needs to be solved by studying intraspecific variability and species limits. They suggested that 
<taxonomicName box="[725,895,262,285]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteropodagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sanguinipes">
<emphasis box="[725,895,262,285]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">H. sanguinipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[951,1096,261,285]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteropodagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="superbum">
<emphasis box="[951,1096,261,285]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">H. superbum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
might be synonymous, as the differences they observed between 
<typeStatus box="[551,599,298,322]" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">type</typeStatus>
material of 
<taxonomicName box="[740,910,298,321]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteropodagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sanguinipes">
<emphasis box="[740,910,298,321]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">H. sanguinipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[967,1112,297,321]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteropodagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="superbum">
<emphasis box="[967,1112,297,321]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">H. superbum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are encompassed within the range of variability in color, size, and especially cercal morphology of examined material of 
<taxonomicName box="[1181,1375,333,357]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteropodagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1181,1375,333,357]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">Heteropodagrion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from various parts of 
<collectingCountry box="[332,427,369,393]" name="Ecuador" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[438,551,369,393]" name="Colombia" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[610,698,370,393]" name="Panama" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">Panama</collectingCountry>
(R. W. Garrison, pers. comm. 
<number box="[1042,1103,369,393]" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" value="2010.0">2010</number>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,646]" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">
Females of the genera 
<emphasis box="[464,827,405,429]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">
<taxonomicName box="[464,660,405,429]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteropodagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Heteropodagrion</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[674,823,406,429]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Dimeragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Dimeragrion</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[887,1008,406,429]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Mesagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[887,1008,406,429]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">Mesagrion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
share a membranous region dorsally between posterior margin of S 
<number box="[491,505,441,465]" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" value="7.0">7</number>
and anterior border of S 
<number box="[782,796,441,465]" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" value="8.0">8</number>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Garrison" box="[811,1050,441,465]" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" refString="Garrison, R. W., von Ellenrieder, N. &amp; Louton, J. A. (2010) Damselfly Genera of the New World. An Illustrated and Annotated Key to the Zygoptera. The John Hopkins University Press. Baltimore. United States of America, xiv + 490 pp, + 24 pls" type="book" year="2010">
Garrison 
<emphasis box="[918,974,441,465]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">et al.</emphasis>
, 
<number box="[989,1050,441,465]" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" value="2010.0">2010</number>
</bibRefCitation>
); females of 
<taxonomicName box="[1195,1389,441,465]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteropodagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1195,1389,441,465]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">Heteropodagrion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[151,273,478,501]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Mesagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,273,478,501]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">Mesagrion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are easy to differentiate by the characters of wing venation and the absence of notches on the prothoracic anterior lobe of 
<emphasis box="[396,597,513,537]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">
<taxonomicName box="[396,593,513,537]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteropodagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Heteropodagrion</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Abdominal color pattern of females of 
<taxonomicName box="[1049,1169,514,537]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteropodagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="croizati">
<emphasis box="[1049,1169,514,537]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">H. croizati</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinctive and separates it at once from its congeners: in 
<taxonomicName box="[581,702,550,573]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Mesagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[581,702,550,573]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">Mesagrion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
there are distal yellow spots, more intense in immature females, which are absent in females of 
<taxonomicName box="[507,700,585,609]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteropodagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[507,700,585,609]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">Heteropodagrion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; in 
<emphasis box="[746,1034,585,609]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">
<taxonomicName box="[746,912,585,609]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteropodagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sanguinipes">H. sanguinipes</taxonomicName>
/ 
<taxonomicName box="[925,1034,585,609]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteropodagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="superbum">superbum</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
all abdominal segments have basal and distal dark rings, whereas in 
<taxonomicName box="[520,639,622,645]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteropodagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="croizati">
<emphasis box="[520,639,622,645]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="68">H. croizati</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
all abdominal segments have a proximal pale ring only.
</paragraph>
